</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="holotype">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
China. Shanxi Province, Ningwu County, Qiuqiangou Village, Luyashan Mountain, alt. 2100m, 25 August 2017, in soil under 
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Picea" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., M. Chen CM023 (BJTC FAN764).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Illustrations</emphasis>
- 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" author="Xu, YY" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="129 - 138" refId="B42" refString="Xu, YY, Guo, LJ, Li, T, Fan, L, 2018. Two new species of Barssia from China. Phytotaxa 374 (2): 129 - 138, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" title="Two new species of Barssia from China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" volume="374" year="2018">Xu et al. (2018</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Balsamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Balsamia luyashanensis" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="luyashanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Balsamia luyashanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also recently described from the Luyashan Mountain of Shanxi Province, China, under 
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Picea" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. So far it is known only from the type locality. The species can be recognized by its red brown ascomata with fine warts, gleba without chambers and irregularly clavate asci (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" author="Xu, YY" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="129 - 138" refId="B42" refString="Xu, YY, Guo, LJ, Li, T, Fan, L, 2018. Two new species of Barssia from China. Phytotaxa 374 (2): 129 - 138, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" title="Two new species of Barssia from China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.374.2.4" volume="374" year="2018">Xu et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The species was similar in appearance of ascomata to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. gunerii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="gunerii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">B. gunerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. hellenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="hellenica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">B. hellenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. gunerii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="gunerii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">B. gunerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by its subglobose to ovoid ascospores and gleba with irregularly sinuous, labyrinth-like veins (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1801-33" author="Dogan, HH" journalOrPublisher="Turkish Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 8" refId="B10" refString="Dogan, HH, Bozok, F, Taskin, H, 2018. A new species of Barssia (Ascomycota, Helvellaceae) from Turkey. Turkish Journal of Botany 42: 1 - 8, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1801-33" title="A new species of Barssia (Ascomycota, Helvellaceae) from Turkey." url="https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1801-33" volume="42" year="2018">
<normalizedToken originalValue="DoÄŸan">Dogan</normalizedToken>
et al. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" author="Hansen, K" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="186 - 204" refId="B14" refString="Hansen, K, Schumacher, T, Skrede, I, Huhtinen, S, Wang, XH, 2019. Pindara revisited-evolution and generic limits in Helvellaceae. Persoonia 42: 186 - 204, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" title="Pindara revisited-evolution and generic limits in Helvellaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" volume="42" year="2019">Hansen et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. hellenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="hellenica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">B. hellenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its ovoid ascospores (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaounas, V" journalOrPublisher="org" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="213 - 219" refId="B18" refString="Kaounas, V, Agnello, C, Alvarado, P, Slavova, M, 2015. Barssia hellenica sp. nov. (Ascomycota, Pezizales), a new hypogeous species from Greece. Ascomycete. org 7 (5): 213 - 219" title="Barssia hellenica sp. nov. (Ascomycota, Pezizales), a new hypogeous species from Greece. Ascomycete." volume="7" year="2015">Kaounas et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" author="Hansen, K" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="186 - 204" refId="B14" refString="Hansen, K, Schumacher, T, Skrede, I, Huhtinen, S, Wang, XH, 2019. Pindara revisited-evolution and generic limits in Helvellaceae. Persoonia 42: 186 - 204, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" title="Pindara revisited-evolution and generic limits in Helvellaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2019.42.07" volume="42" year="2019">Hansen et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
